# StockAnalyzer Pro - API Configuration Template
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your own API keys

# =============================================================================
# REDDIT API CREDENTIALS (Required for social sentiment analysis)
# =============================================================================
# How to get Reddit API credentials:
# 1. Go to: https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps
# 2. Log in to your Reddit account (or create one)
# 3. Scroll to bottom, click "create another app..."
# 4. Fill in:
#    - name: StockAnalyzer
#    - type: Select "script"
#    - description: Stock sentiment analysis tool
#    - redirect uri: http://localhost:8080
# 5. Click "create app"
# 6. Copy your credentials:
#    - Client ID: (14 characters under app name)
#    - Client Secret: (27 characters, click "show")
#
# Cost: FREE (60 requests/minute limit)

REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=your_reddit_client_id_here
REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=your_reddit_client_secret_here
REDDIT_USER_AGENT=StockAnalyzer:v1.0 (by /u/your_reddit_username)

# =============================================================================
# CLAUDE/ANTHROPIC API KEY (Required for advanced sentiment analysis)
# =============================================================================
# How to get Claude API key:
# 1. Go to: https://console.anthropic.com/
# 2. Sign up for an account
# 3. Navigate to "API Keys" section
# 4. Click "Create Key"
# 5. Name it: "StockAnalyzer"
# 6. Copy the key (starts with "sk-ant-api03-")
#
# Cost estimate:
# - Sentiment analysis: ~$0.002 per article
# - Full S&P 500 analysis (~50,000 articles): ~$100 one-time
# - Incremental updates: ~$1-5/month
#
# NOTE: In production, users will provide their own API keys via the app UI.
# This .env file is for development only.

NEWS_API_KEY=your_claude_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: News API (Currently not used, reserved for future features)
# =============================================================================
# Uncomment if you want to add additional news sources in the future
# NEWS_API_KEY_ACTUAL=your_news_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTE
# =============================================================================
# NEVER commit the real .env file to git!
# The .env file with your actual API keys should remain local only.
# Only this .env.example template should be in the repository.
#
# For production distribution:
# - Users provide their own API keys via the app's settings UI
# - Keys are stored securely in macOS Keychain (or equivalent on other platforms)
# - No API keys are bundled with the distributed application
